The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bagan get down to business today
                                                                                                                                                                                           Bagan get down to business today
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohun Bagan will start a new season under a new coach on Friday when they take on Peerless in a Premier Division match of the Sahara Calcutta Football League at their home ground.         
	Peerless lost their first match to George Telegraph in the League.         
	Karim Bencharifa, the century-old clubs new foreigner coach, is looking forward to the encounter as a new experience. Its a chance to prove ourselves in front of our fans, he said on Thursday.         
	Although we are not 100 per cent prepared, we want to make a winning start. Winning the first match of a season is very important. That will stand us in good stead, he added.         
	Jose Ramirez Barreto, who has been the mainstay of the green-and-maroon brigade for the last few years, said as the senior-most player, he was willing to take extra responsibility and guide the juniors.         
	Im the only senior footballer in the team, so I have to take more responsibility, the Brazilian said.         
	With the coach promising attacking football, the fans can hope for an entertaining afternoon on Friday.                                                                                                                          
